{"id": "duc04-testb-6:9#28", "contents": "The repatriation of the North Koreans has been met with concerns, particularly from a North Korean human rights group and Japanese tourists who have visited the region. Reports from South Korea's Yonhap News Agency suggest that as many as 150 North Koreans were sent back to their country despite presenting petitions for political asylum. The situation in North Korea is dire, with the country facing its fourth winter of chronic food shortages, having harvested only 3 million tons of grain this year - a significant shortfall from the minimum 4.5 million tons needed to sustain its population of 23 million people."}
